In 2018, President Donald Trump adopted a National Biodefense Strategy.
Anticipating such shortages, the biodefense strategy calls for setting up excess manufacturing capacity to produce these necessities quickly in an emergency.
The National Biodefense Strategy is supposed to untangle that mess.
The administration official said the steering committee outlined in the biodefense strategy was superseded by the Coronavirus Task Force.
The official said Trump created the biodefense strategy to improve response time in situations such as the coronavirus pandemic, and it's working.